##############################################################################
#   This file explains how to set up and run the calibration of the CCLM 5.0 #
#   Written 4/28/15 by Katie Osterried.                                      #
##############################################################################


Steps for setting up and running the calibration:

1. First, prepare the INPUT_ORG_reference, INPUT_PHY_reference, and INPUT_IO_reference
   files located in: ~/calibration/input/INPUT_ORG,  ~/calibration/input/INPUT_PHY,
   and ~/calibration/input/INPUT_IO.  

2. Then, change the minima and maxima for the parameters in the generate_input.sh script
   if needed (found in ~/calibration/input)

3. Clean out the ~/calibration/input/INPUT_ORG, ~/calibration/input/INPUT_PHY 
   and ~/calibration/input/INPUT_IO folders.  !! Don't delete the reference files!!

4. Run the generate_input.sh script to make all of the INPUT_ORG, INPUT_PHY,
   and INPUT_IO files.

5. Clean out anything that is in the /scratch/daint/ksilver/calibration/run folder.

6. Change the job_reference.sh script if needed (found in ~/calibration/jobs)

7. Run the prepare_jobs.sh script to generate the run folders and copy the variable
   input files to the run folders.  

8. Prepare and copy the other INPUT_ files to the /scratch/daint/ksilver/calibration/run folder.

9. Copy the cclm executable to the /scratch/daint/ksilver/calibration/run folder.  

10. Use the run_calibration.sh script to submit all of the Slurm batch jobs 
    (found in ~/calibration)  



